<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4656593>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2: A-B, Stenopus hispidus (Olivier, 1811). A, Female, cl 12.4 mm, lateral view (MZUSP 35268). B, Ovigerous female, cl 21 mm, lateral view (MZUSP 35269). C-D, Enoplometopus antillensis Lütken, 1865, photographed in situ in Trindade, but escaped before it could be collected. E-F, Parribacus antarcticus (Lund, 1793), male, cl 91 mm, dorsal and ventral views, respectively (MZUSP 35271). Scales: A, 12 mm. B, 21 mm. E-F, 90 mm. Photographs by JBM." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4656593/files/figure.png" .

